	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I just ran into these guys for my first time today. I've been in EW for about a week now, and have taken part in killing the chief 3 times, and seen others do it twice. These kills have included inside and outside the fort. I really don't believe there is a pattern to the avengers spawning. It seems to be completely random. It isn't caused by looting because the chief droped for my group twice with no avengers. The best way to deal with them is to just drag the chief outside the fort to give yourself some running room. Have someone with track hit it right after he dies, and if they are there, run. They do run at slightly below sow speed, so you can get away if you have sow on. Alot of people have said to run to CC zone if they come, but it is safer to run them to one of the other zones. To get to CC, you have to click on the bars, then the snowball... while you are being beaten on from behind. Just make sure to shout that you are coming so people can clear out. It is also a good idea to shout when you are killing the chief so that groups around the fort know to be on the lookout. If you get jumped by these guys and have no warning, you have no chance.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
