	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Nifty critters ... I have only seen the fortress so far while passing through it, on my way to the Crystal Caverns.I think it is actually cool that a death-squad spawns to avenge the death of a powerful leader.<BR>
<BR>
In these discussions I see people who have them spawn on them, and those who kill the Chief without the Avenger-pop. Some people post that the Avenger pop is random ... however, I clearly see a pattern based on the messages here.<BR>
<BR>
When someone kills the Chief, and he does NOT drop the Ry'Gorr BattleMail or the Spear, they are safe ... no Avengers spawn.<BR>
<BR>
However, as soon as the BattleMail or the Spear are dropped (adn consequentially looted), the Avengers pop and do a sweep of the area to kill all. It seems that whenever he drops the special loot, they pop ...<BR>
<BR>
Anyway, to prevent this, have someone in the party Ninja-Loot the Chief when he dies. If he has the loot, he should yell so, and the group should make an emergency Evac. Mmm .. thinking about that, it might be better to evac ALWAYS! :)
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
